            <title>[GROOVY-9691] Method call &quot;main&quot; is replaced with StaticMethodCallExpression in script</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9691</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider the following Gradle build script snippet:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
sourceSets {
    main {
        java { srcDirs = [] }
        groovy { srcDirs = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;src/main&apos;&lt;/span&gt;] }
    }
    test {
        java { srcDirs = [] }
        groovy { srcDirs = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;src/test&apos;&lt;/span&gt;] }
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When opened in an editor, Groovy transforms &quot;main&quot; to a reference to &quot;static void main(String[])&quot;.  This negatively impacts the editing experience because Closure is not a match for String and the IDE gets quite confused.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This applies to any script (or class with a static main method) that uses &quot;main&quot; as a method call within a closure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
